\u2022 Harness powerful new battlefield.EN: • Harness powerful new battlefield tactics by boosting and protecting your troops\n• The Grand Warden toughens all nearby troops and can make them temporarily invincible!\n• He jumps, he flies - fit the Grand Warden into any strategy and make your army shine

\u2022 This massive, long-range weapon o.EN: • This massive, long-range weapon obliterates poorly prepared attacking armies\n• Volleys of explosive shells clobber tough troops and wear down others near the blasts\n• Eagle Artillery only activates after many troops have been deployed, leaving the door open for tactical strikes and cunning multi-phase attacks!

\u2022 Request reinforcement Spells, not.EN: • Request reinforcement Spells, not just Troops, starting from Clan Castle level 4\n• Donated Spells receive all existing Clan Perks benefits\n• Freeze Spell is now unlocked at Town Hall 9 and has slightly longer duration on lower levels

\u2022 Town Hall destruction no longer g.EN: • Town Hall destruction no longer grants a Shield - bring your Town Hall inside!\n• You can attack while shielded at any time for just a small Shield reduction\n• Get Shield at 30% destruction, more at 60%, but only when a sizable army attacks

\u2022 Guard protects you from attacks a.EN:
• Guard protects you from attacks and lets you attack others all you want
• Get free Guard when Shields expire and play freely without worry of being attacked
• Higher Leagues grant more free Guard - Titan I & Legend players get 100% coverage!
• 2 hours of extra Guard is available in the Shop every day

\u2022 Town Halls now hold lots of avail.EN: • Town Halls now hold lots of available loot - destroy them in battle for a big payout!\n• League Bonuses are bigger than ever, but scale with your destruction percentage\n• Trophy offers get bigger and Trophy losses lower the higher your League!

\u2022 Battle time limit has been increa.EN:
• Battle time limit has been increased by 30 seconds
• Goblins now target the Town Hall and Clan Castle for 2x damage
• Rearm costs for all Traps have been massively reduced
• Reload costs for X-Bows have been massively reduced
• Large amounts of Healers now have reduced effectiveness on the same unit
• Army boosts have been reduced to 5 Gems for 1 hour of boost
• Cost for finding a match and ‘Nexting´ reduced for TH10
• Clan War Preparation Day has been reduced to 23 hours
• Troop combat and pathfinding AI has been polished up and tightened
• Available loot percentage on Town Hall levels 6-10 has been slightly increased
• Villages one Town Hall level lower are now worth slightly less loot
• The playing field and Troop deployment area have both been expanded (outlying obstacles have been automatically moved)

\u2022 Two new achievements have been ad.EN:
• Two new achievements have been added: Anti-Artillery and Sharing is Caring
• Troop/Spell donation interface has been revamped and now shows existing donations
• Troops in Barracks can now be queued in sequence, similarly to the Spell Factory
• The Clan War button now animates when a War attack starts
• Active Shield or Guard can now be manually dismissed by tapping on the icon
• You can now be offline a bit longer before being made vulnerable to attack
• A special sound plays when finding a multiplayer target after 10 seconds of searching
• A special sound plays when no multiplayer targets are found and a search is cancelled
• Personal Break online-time limit has been reduced to 3 hours
• Personal Break limit is now extended instead of reset in some cases
• Multiplayer matchmaking is less likely to offer opponents under your Town Hall level (only below Champion League)

These important documents govern your relationship with our games, containing beneficial information for anyone who chooses to play. For more information, visit our forums.

Clan Games are all about completing Chal.EN: Clan Games are all about completing Challenges and earning points together with your clanmates. The more points you earn as a clan, the better your rewards will be when the Games end. Be sure to involve your clanmates: the more people you have, the easier it will be to climb the reward tiers!

Challenges are meant to test your streng.EN: Challenges are meant to test your strength in different areas. Completing a challenge within its time limit awards your clan points. Challenges vary in difficulty. If one of them appears too difficult for you, ask your clanmates to take it. Should you take on a Challenge you cannot finish, you can trash it. Note that you have to wait for a while after trashing before being able to take on a new Challenge.

When the Clan Games end, it's time to en.EN: When the Clan Games end, it's time to enjoy the rewards! Rewards come in several different tiers that get unlocked as your clan collects points from finished Challenges. Everyone who participated in the Clan Games by completing at least one Challenge will be eligible to pick one reward from each reward tier. Unclaimed rewards will be lost after 7 days.

Siege Machines are a new and alternative.EN: Siege Machines are a new and alternative way to deliver your Clan Castle reinforcements. Rather than deploying your Clan Castle troops from the periphery of the map, Siege Machines allow you to deliver them straight into the heart of the enemy´s Village! The Siege Workshop allows you to build a Siege Machine for yourself or your Clan mates can donate one to you. Keep in mind your Clan Castle must be at least level 6 in order to fit a Siege Machine.

Each Siege Machine specializes in a diff.EN: Each Siege Machine specializes in a different way of delivering destruction. You can build multiple Siege Machines, that way you can choose which one you want to use at the start of the battle. Furthermore, if you prefer to not use your Siege Machine, you can still deploy your Clan Castle reinforcements the old fashioned way by toggling to the Clan Castle banner in the troop bar. Don´t forget to request Clan Castle troops from your Clan mates! Having an empty Clan Castle means your Siege Machines will be empty as well. There is no wrong choice in which Siege Machine you choose. Ultimately, it´s up to you to decide which one is the right one that complements your Clan Castle troop combination!

<cFCE27F>What are Clan War Leagues?</c>\.EN: <cFCE27F>What are Clan War Leagues?</c>\n\nClan War Leagues is the ultimate contest for clans. It is a monthly league that puts your clan against seven others to determine which is the best. You will fight against the seven other clans in seven wars over seven days. At the end, clans that have earned the most stars are promoted to higher leagues while others stay or are demoted. Next month you will resume where you left off. The higher you can get, the more rewards and glory you can earn. Keep climbing upwards with your clan and you may eventually become the best in the world!

<cFCE27F>How can my clan participate?</c.EN:
<cFCE27F>How can my clan participate?</c>

Leaders and Co-leaders can sign your Clan up during the opt-in period. If you are participating for the first time, you will be placed into a league tier based on the strength of your fifteen strongest members. Once seven other Clans from your league tier have been found, preparation for the first round will begin immediately!<cFCE27F>

My Clan isn't very strong. Should we participate?</c>

Yes! As long as you have at least fifteen members, you should participate. You can earn great rewards even if you don't get promoted to a higher league tier!

<cFCE27F>What do we get out of Clan War.EN:
<cFCE27F>What do we get out of Clan War Leagues?</c>

Glory of course! But there are also exclusive rewards that you can only get from participating in Clan War Leagues! Earning Stars during battle week will earn you League Medals. The higher your league tier, the more League Medals you will earn. You can exchange your hard-earned League Medals in the Shop for rare Magic Items and other unique prizes.

<cFCE27F>Are there other ways to earn League Medals?</c>

Clan leadership can award a limited number of bonus Medals to anyone participating, even if they didn't fight! You get more and bigger bonuses in higher league tiers, with each win giving you an extra one!

<cFCE27F>What is the Battle Week? </c>\\.EN:
<cFCE27F>What is the Battle Week? </c>

During each battle week, your clan will be grouped with seven other clans from your league tier. Over the next seven days, your clan will war with each of the other clans to determine who's the best in your group! Clans that do well can get promoted to the next higher league tier while the bottom performing clans will get dropped to the next tier below your current one.

When a battle week starts, your clan will first enter into preparation period for your first war day. During the preparation day you can choose the participants for the next war from everyone who signed up. After 24 hours have passed, the first war day will begin. Simultaneously, preparations for the second war day will also begin!

<cFCE27F>How is the leaderboard ranked?<.EN: <cFCE27F>How is the leaderboard ranked?</c>\n\nYou can check where your Clan currently stands in comparison to the 7 other Clans in your League group by viewing the Leaderboard. The Leaderboard displays the status of your Clan's performance throughout the Battle Week and is based on the total number of Stars earned. Your clan earns an additional 10 Stars for each won war. The more Stars you earn, the higher your Clan will rank!

Your reward limit depends on your clan\u.EN: Your reward limit depends on your clan´s league level and position at the end of the season. You earn at least 20% of the rewards and 10% more for each obtained star. For 8 or more stars you earn the full reward.

Legend League is where elite players bat.EN:
Legend League is where elite players battle to see who has the best attacks and base layouts. Each day everyone in Legend League has a fixed number of attacks and defenses. You can gain up to <num> trophies and cannot lose any when attacking. There is no searching time after pressing the Attack button.

If your trophy count is too low when a league day ends, you will drop from Legend League and return to the normal multiplayer system.

When you join Legend League you may get a reduced number of attacks and defenses for the first day.

In Legend League you can use a different.EN: In Legend League you can use a different layout for defending from the one other players see when they visit your base. You can change the layout and also defending Clan Castle troops in the Defense tab of the Attack menu. Defense settings will remain in use until you change them or drop out of the Legend League.\n\nDefenses can happen even while you are playing in your village. In Legend League you will not lose any resources from a defense and can still play while being attacked.

You don't get Shield or Guard when attac.EN: You don't get Shield or Guard when attacked in the Legend League. However, it's still possible to take a break by purchasing Shields. If your Shield is active when the league day changes you get to skip both attacking and defending for the next league day. It's not possible to purchase or remove Shield for the current league day, but only for the next day.\n\nIf you have purchased a Shield for the following day, but drop out of Legend League the Shield will remain effective in the normal multiplayer system.

\u300a\u90e8\u843d\u51b2\u7a81\u300b\u90.EN:
《部落冲突》适龄提示：
1）本游戏是一款战争策略类游戏，适用于年满12周岁及以上的用户，建议未成年人在家长监护下使用游戏产品。
2）本游戏以荒蛮原始的孤岛为背景，讲述了原始部落为生存而相互抗争的故事，涉及的情节、环境、场景均为虚构，不会与现实生活相混淆。游戏玩法基于一定难度的思维判断，设有竞技对抗比赛，鼓励玩家提升和挑战自我。游戏中有基于文字和语音的陌生人社交系统。
3）根据国家相关要求，游戏中有用户实名认证系统，未通过实名认证的用户不可进入游戏；认证为未成年人的用户除周五、周六、周日及法定节假日每日20时至21时外其他时间均不可进入游戏。
游戏中部分玩法和道具需要付费。根据腾讯健康系统管理规定，认证为未成年人的用户将接受以
管理：
未满12周岁的用户不能付费；12周岁以上未满16周岁的未成年人用户，单次充值金额不得超过50元人民币，每月充值金额累计不得超过200元人民币；16周岁以上的未成年人用户，单次充值金额不得超过100元人民币，每月充值金额累计不得超过400元人民币。
4）本游戏内所包含的对抗玩法需要玩家进行策略规划和推理判断，有助于帮助玩家提升逻辑思维能力。游戏设有需组队进行的大型团队任务和比赛，鼓励玩家互相配合完成比赛，有助于培养玩家的团队协作能力。游戏提供了丰富的社交系统，包括好友、公会等，玩家之间可以互相交流，互相配合，共同完成游戏任务，有助于促进玩家的社会交流，维持良好的社群关系。
